areaname: Ute Mountain Area, Colorado and New Mexico
exportmetadata:
The "7 1zvc-Battlerock clay loam, 0 to 6 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "7 2s282-Hamburn clay loam, 0 to 6 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 35 - Battlerock clay loam, 0 to 6 percent slopes" project". 

The "22 1zvd-Claysprings very stony clay loam, 12 to 65 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "22 2s283-Claysprings very stony clay loam, 12 to 65 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 35 - Claysprings very stony clay loam, 12 to 65 percent slopes" project". 

The "45 1zxh-Jeddito loamy fine sand, 0 to 2 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "45 2s27t-Jeddito loamy fine sand, 0 to 2 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 35 - Jeddito loamy fine sand, 0 to 2 percent slopes" project". 

The "76 1zvs-Pogo loam, 0 to 2 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "76 2tkxp-Pogo loam, 0 to 2 percent slopes, frequently flooded MLRA 36" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 36 - Pogo loam, 0 to 2 percent slopes" project". 

The "80 1zvt-Ravola clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "80 2s287-Ravola clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 35 - Ravola clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" project". 

The "82 1zxn-Ravola very fine sandy loam, 1 to 3 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "82 2s27z-Ravola very fine sandy loam, 1 to 3 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 35 - Ravola very fine sandy loam, 1 to 3 percent slopes" project". 

The "91 13192-Sharps loam, dry, 6 to 12 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "91 2tkxq-Sharps loam, 6 to 12 percent slopes MLRA 36" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 36 - Sharps loam, dry, 6 to 12 percent slopes" project". 

The "97 1zwp-Sideshow silty clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "97 2tkxr-Sideshow silty clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes MLRA 36" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 36 - Sideshow silty clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" project". 

The "98 1zwq-Sideshow silty clay loam, 3 to 6 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "98 2tkxs-Sideshow silty clay loam, 3 to 6 percent slopes MLRA 36" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 36 - Sideshow silty clay loam, 3 to 6 percent slopes" project". 

The "122 1zx1-Wauquie-Dolcan-Rock outcrop complex, 25 to 80 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "122 2w593-Wauquie-Dolcan-Rock outcrop complex, 25 to 80 percent slopes MLRA 36" map unit as a result of the "SDJR - MLRA 36 - Wauquie-Dolcan-Rock outcrop complex, 25 to 80 percent slopes" project". 

These projects were part of the Soil Data Join Recorrelation Initiative (SDJR). The tabular database was edited and populated according to guidance in National Instruction (NI-305) exhibits A and B.
